entry.content:
&lt;h2 id=&#34;no-its-not-a-pi&#34;&gt;No it&amp;rsquo;s not a Pi&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s an &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.hardkernel.com/shop/odroid-mc1-my-cluster-one-with-32-cpu-cores-and-8gb-dram/&#34;&gt;ODroid MC1&lt;/a&gt;,
a board based on the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.hardkernel.com/shop/odroid-xu4-special-price/&#34;&gt;ODroid XU4&lt;/a&gt;,
an SBC that is multiple times more powerful than the Pi (however, I&amp;rsquo;ll be using an &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.hardkernel.com/shop/odroid-hc1-home-cloud-one/&#34;&gt;ODroid HC1&lt;/a&gt; as it has a SATA port in the back that I&amp;rsquo;ll be taking advantage of).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;an-odroid-what&#34;&gt;An ODroid What?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ODroid XU4, which has (to quote the landing page):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Samsung Exynos 5422 Cortex™-A15 2Ghz and Cortex™-A7 Octa core CPUs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mali-T628 MP6(OpenGL ES 3.1/2.0/1.1 and OpenCL 1.2 Full profile)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2Gbyte LPDDR3 RAM PoP stacked&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now, sure there is a 2GB model of the Pi, heck, there&amp;rsquo;s even a 4GB model of the Pi, but nothing the Pi has compares to an overpowered 8 core processor, plus a GPU featuring OpenGL (ES) and OpenCL support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you still don&amp;rsquo;t think that&amp;rsquo;s good enough, you can check that &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.hardkernel.com/shop/odroid-xu4-special-price/&#34;&gt;landing page&lt;/a&gt; for some benchmarks.&lt;/p&gt;
